text: {{Infobox Writer | name = Mihai Eminescu | image = Eminescu.jpg | caption = Mihai Eminescu as a student in Vienna, 1869 | birth_date = | birth_place = Botoşani, Moldavia (region of Romania) | death_date = | death_place = Bucharest, Romania | occupation = Poet and journalist | genre = | movement = Romanticism | notableworks = | website = }} Mihai Eminescu (pronunciation in Romanian: ) (January 15, 1850 – June 15, 1889), born Mihail Eminovici, was a late Romantic poet, the best-known and most influential Romanian poet. Famous poems include Luceafărul ("Evening Star"), Odă în metru antic (Ode in ancient meter), and the five Scrisori (Epistles/Satires). Eminescu was active in the Junimea literary society, and served as editor of Timpul, the official newspaper of the Conservative Party.
